---
import BaseLayout from '../../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro'
---
<BaseLayout title="Install BridgeAIChat Agent" description="Install and configure a BridgeAIChat agent on a remote device.">
  <section class="surface">
    <div class="eyebrow">Install</div>
    <h1>Turn a machine into a BridgeAIChat agent.</h1>
    <p class="lede">
      Each agent device keeps its own AI CLI, working directory, and runtime context. The installer handles the local
      config file, gateway URL prompt, and optional startup-service registration.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="section-gap grid two">
    <div class="card stack">
      <div class="eyebrow">Preferred</div>
      <h2>Install with Homebrew</h2>
      <pre>brew install bridge-ai-chat/tap/bridge-agent
bash "$(brew --prefix)/share/bridge-agent/install-agent.sh"</pre>
      <p>This path installs the binary onto <code>PATH</code> and writes configuration to <code>~/.bridge-agent/agent.yaml</code>.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="card stack">
      <div class="eyebrow">Fallback</div>
      <h2>Use the release archive</h2>
      <pre>tar -xzf bridge-agent_v0.1.0-beta.1_darwin_arm64.tar.gz
cd bridge-agent_v0.1.0-beta.1_darwin_arm64
bash install-agent.sh</pre>
      <p>The release installer works from the extracted bundle and can still install the agent as a background service.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section-gap grid two">
    <div class="card">
      <div class="eyebrow">Requirements</div>
      <h2>What must exist on the device</h2>
      <ul class="list tight">
        <li><code>tmux</code> required for Codex and tmux-backed tools; not required for Claude with <code>direct: true</code></li>
        <li>Tailscale must be able to reach the gateway</li>
        <li>An AI CLI must already be installed locally (Claude, Codex, or Ollama)</li>
        <li>The <code>cmd</code>, <code>args</code>, and <code>direct</code> flags in <code>agent.yaml</code> must match the installed CLI</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="card stack">
      <div class="eyebrow">Example</div>
      <h2>Claude config block</h2>
      <pre>device:
  id: macbook-pro
  name: My MacBook Pro

tools:
  claude:
    cmd: claude
    args: ["-p"]
    continue_args: ["--continue", "-p"]
    direct: true

default_tool: claude

gateway:
  url: ws://100.101.102.103:8080/agent</pre>
      <p><code>direct: true</code> is required for Claude. Use Tailscale IPs or MagicDNS names for the gateway URL.</p>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
